com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models

Class CreateMessageOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models.QueueServiceOptions
      • com.microsoft.windowsazure.services.queue.models.CreateMessageOptions

  • public class CreateMessageOptions
extends QueueServiceOptions
    Represents the options that may be set on the Queue service for createMessage requests. These options include a server response timeout for the request, the visibility timeout to set on the created message, and the time-to-live value to set on the message.

      • setVisibilityTimeoutInSeconds

        public CreateMessageOptions setVisibilityTimeoutInSeconds(java.lang.Integer visibilityTimeoutInSeconds)
        Sets the message visibility timeout in seconds value to set on messages when making a createMessage request. This allows messages to be loaded into the queue but not become visible until the visibility timeout has passed. Valid visibility timeout values range from 0 to 604800 seconds (0 to 7 days), and must be less than the time-to-live value.

        The visibilityTimeoutInSeconds value only affects calls made on methods where this CreateMessageOptions instance is passed as a parameter.

        Parameters:
        visibilityTimeoutInSeconds - The length of time during which the message will be invisible, starting when it is added to the queue, or 0 to make the message visible immediately. This value must be greater than or equal to zero and less than or equal to the time-to-live value.
        Returns:
        A reference to this CreateMessageOptions instance.

      • setTimeToLiveInSeconds

        public CreateMessageOptions setTimeToLiveInSeconds(java.lang.Integer timeToLiveInSeconds)
        Sets the message time-to-live timeout value to set on messages when making a createMessage request. This is the maximum duration in seconds for the message to remain in the queue after it is created. Valid timeToLiveInSeconds values range from 0 to 604800 seconds (0 to 7 days), with the default value set to seven days.

        The timeToLiveInSeconds value only affects calls made on methods where this CreateMessageOptions instance is passed as a parameter.

        Parameters:
        timeToLiveInSeconds - The maximum time to allow the message to be in the queue, in seconds.
        Returns:
        A reference to this CreateMessageOptions instance.
